To Macrobius our own learned Antiquary Mr. Selden assents (in his Diis Syriis)


and proves all the Syrian and Egyptian Gods to have been representations of the Vertues of (that Hermaphrodite-light) the Sun and Moon; the Ancients thinking that the Soul of God-saviour, either had been or was to be assumed into those Planets, after he had performed his saving Gests upon Earth, his [animus] the divine part of it, into the Sun; his [anima] or humane Soul into the Moon, as being a Saviour of both Sexes: upon which reason they called Apollo [
